🧠 2) DSA — ANAGRAM PROBLEMS
🔹 What is an Anagram?

Two strings containing the same characters with the same frequency but possibly in different order

Example:

"listen" ↔ "silent"
🔹 GS-Level Solution — Count Map
from collections import Counter

def is_anagram(s1, s2):
    return Counter(s1) == Counter(s2)
O(n) time, O(n) space
Handles duplicates automatically
🔹 Sorting Approach
def is_anagram(s1, s2):
    return sorted(s1) == sorted(s2)
O(n log n) time, O(n) space
Simpler, but less efficient than Counter
🔹 Follow-ups
Unicode / multi-language support → normalize before comparison
Streaming / huge strings → count frequency in chunks
Case-insensitive → convert to lowercase
Ignore spaces/punctuation → regex cleaning
🔹 Production Considerations
Input validation → reject non-string inputs
Logging → record invalid attempts
Memory efficiency → avoid unnecessary copies for large strings
